column1: Prevalence of Psychological, Physical and Sexual Spousal Violence

column2: Prevalence of physical, sexual and physical and/or sexual violence, among ever-married women 15-64 years

column1: 1 Proportion of ever-married women and girls aged 15-64 years subjected to physical, sexual or psychological violence by a current or former husband: Ever and last 12 months
Violence against Women, Attitude and Experiences (Ever Married Women): Questions 1206 A or B (psychological); 1207A or B (physical); 1208 A or B (sexual). Code (1) for all

Computation Method:
This indicator calls for breakdown by form of violence and by age group and yields the following for each form of violence or forms of violence: 
1. Physical violence: Numberof ever-married women aged 15 -64 who experienced physical violence by a current or former husband ever and previous 12 months divided by the number of ever-married women (aged 15 -64) in the population multiplied by 100                                                                                                                                                                                   2. Sexual violence: Number of ever-married women (aged 15 -64 years) who experience sexual violence by a current or former husband ever and previous 12 months divided by the number of ever-married women (aged 15 -64 years) in the population multiplied by 100                                                                                                                                                                                                         3. Psychological violence: Number of ever-married women and girls (aged 15 years and above) who experience psychological violence by a current or former husband in ever and previous 12 months divided by the number of ever-married women (aged 15 -64 years) multiplied by 100                                                                                                                                                                                             4. Any form of physical and/or sexual violence: Number of ever-married women (aged 15 -64 years ) who experience physical and/or sexual violence by a current or former husband in ever and previous 12 months divided by the number of ever-married women (aged 15 -64 years) multiplied by 100                                                                                                                                                                                      5. Any form of physical and/or sexual  violence: Number of ever-married women (aged 15 -64 years ) who experience  by a current or former husband ever andprevious 12 months divided by the number of ever-married women (aged 15 -64 years and above) multiplied by 100
